# Load the essays and similarity results
essays_df = pd.read_csv('./train500.csv')
similarity_df = pd.read_csv('./similarity_results_500.csv')

# 1. Find essays containing "PROPER_NAME"
proper_name_essays = essays_df[essays_df['full_text'].str.contains('PROPER_NAME', case=False)]
proper_name_ids = proper_name_essays['essay_id'].tolist()

# 2. Filter similarity results where neither essay contains "PROPER_NAME"
filtered_similarity_df = similarity_df[
    (~similarity_df['Essay A ID'].isin(proper_name_ids)) &
    (~similarity_df['Essay B ID'].isin(proper_name_ids))
]

# 3. Find the top 5 most similar pairs for each method
top_5_smpc = filtered_similarity_df[filtered_similarity_df['Method'] == 'SMPC'].nlargest(5, 'Similarity Score')[['Essay A ID', 'Essay B ID', 'Similarity Score']]
top_5_fingerprint = filtered_similarity_df[filtered_similarity_df['Method'] == 'Fingerprint'].nlargest(5, 'Similarity Score')[['Essay A ID', 'Essay B ID', 'Similarity Score']]
top_5_cosine = filtered_similarity_df[filtered_similarity_df['Method'] == 'Cosine'].nlargest(5, 'Similarity Score')[['Essay A ID', 'Essay B ID', 'Similarity Score']]

# Display the results
print("Top 5 SMPC Similarity Pairs:")
print(top_5_smpc)

print("\nTop 5 Fingerprint Similarity Pairs:")
print(top_5_fingerprint)

print("\nTop 5 Cosine Similarity Pairs:")
print(top_5_cosine)

# Create a dictionary to map essay ID to text length for quick lookup
essay_length_map = essays_df.set_index('essay_id')['full_text'].str.len().to_dict()

# Calculate combined text length for each comparison
similarity_df['Combined Text Length'] = similarity_df['Essay A ID'].map(essay_length_map) + similarity_df['Essay B ID'].map(essay_length_map)

# Define a function to plot time vs. combined length for a given method
def plot_time_complexity(method_name):
    method_df = similarity_df[similarity_df['Method'] == method_name]

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.scatter(method_df['Combined Text Length'], method_df['Time Taken'], alpha=0.6)
    plt.title(f'Time Complexity for {method_name} Method')
    plt.xlabel('Combined Text Length (chars)')
    plt.ylabel('Time Taken (s)')
    plt.ylim(0, 0.015)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()

# Plot for each method
plot_time_complexity('SMPC')
plot_time_complexity('Fingerprint')
plot_time_complexity('Cosine')

Find How the Average Pair's Time Differed, by Method¶

In [ ]:
# Filter results for SMPC, Cosine, and Fingerprint
smpc_results = similarity_df[similarity_df['Method'] == 'SMPC']
cosine_results = similarity_df[similarity_df['Method'] == 'Cosine']
fingerprint_results = similarity_df[similarity_df['Method'] == 'Fingerprint']

# Merge all three methods' results based on Essay A ID and Essay B ID
merged_results = pd.merge(smpc_results, cosine_results, on=['Essay A ID', 'Essay B ID'], suffixes=('_SMPC', '_Cosine'))
merged_results = pd.merge(merged_results, fingerprint_results, on=['Essay A ID', 'Essay B ID'])

# Rename columns for clarity in merged results
merged_results.rename(columns={'Time Taken': 'Time Taken_Fingerprint'}, inplace=True)

# Calculate time differences for each pair of methods
merged_results['Cosine - SMPC'] = merged_results['Time Taken_Cosine'] - merged_results['Time Taken_SMPC']
merged_results['Fingerprint - SMPC'] = merged_results['Time Taken_Fingerprint'] - merged_results['Time Taken_SMPC']
merged_results['Cosine - Fingerprint'] = merged_results['Time Taken_Cosine'] - merged_results['Time Taken_Fingerprint']

# Calculate average time differences
average_cosine_smpc = merged_results['Cosine - SMPC'].mean()
average_fingerprint_smpc = merged_results['Fingerprint - SMPC'].mean()
average_cosine_fingerprint = merged_results['Cosine - Fingerprint'].mean()

# Display the results
print(f"Average time difference (Cosine - SMPC): {average_cosine_smpc:.6f} seconds")
print(f"Average time difference (Fingerprint - SMPC): {average_fingerprint_smpc:.6f} seconds")
print(f"Average time difference (Cosine - Fingerprint): {average_cosine_fingerprint:.6f} seconds")

Average time difference (Cosine - SMPC): -0.001156 seconds
Average time difference (Fingerprint - SMPC): 0.000504 seconds
Average time difference (Cosine - Fingerprint): -0.001660 seconds

Generate Latex Tables With First Sentences¶

In [ ]:
# Function to clean up the text by removing newlines and double spaces
def clean_text(text):
    return text.replace('\n', ' ').replace('  ', ' ').strip()

# Function to retrieve the first sentence of an essay by its ID
def get_first_sentence(essay_id):
    full_text = essays_df[essays_df['essay_id'] == essay_id]['full_text'].values[0]
    first_sentence = full_text.split('.')[0] + '.'
    return clean_text(first_sentence)

# Function to generate LaTeX tables with cleaned text and better column formatting
def generate_latex_table_pair_format_cleaned(pairs, method_name):
    latex_code = f"\\begin{{table}}[h!]\n\\centering\n\\caption{{Top 5 {method_name} Similarity Pairs for the Subset of 500 Essays}}\n"
    latex_code += "\\begin{tabular}{|c|m{3cm}|m{10cm}|}\n\\hline\n"
    latex_code += "SCORE & ESSAY IDS & FIRST SENTENCES \\\\\n\\hline\n"

    for i, (essay_id_1, essay_id_2, similarity_score) in enumerate(pairs, 1):

        latex_code += f"{similarity_score:.2f} & "
        essay_1_sentence = get_first_sentence(essay_id_1)
        essay_2_sentence = get_first_sentence(essay_id_2)

        # Clean essay IDs too, just in case
        essay_id_1_cleaned = clean_text(essay_id_1)
        essay_id_2_cleaned = clean_text(essay_id_2)

        # Add pair information to the LaTeX table with cleaned text and bolded "Essay A/B"

        latex_code += f"\\textbf{{Essay A}}: {essay_id_1_cleaned} \\newline \\textbf{{Essay B}}: {essay_id_2_cleaned} & "
        latex_code += f"\\textbf{{Essay A}}: {essay_1_sentence} \\newline \\textbf{{Essay B}}: {essay_2_sentence} \\\\\n\\hline\n"

    latex_code += "\\end{tabular}\n\\end{table}\n"
    return latex_code
